An early-morning intelligence operation conducted by police officers from the Stabilisation Team and Provincial Special Investigation and Tracing Team led to the arrest of two suspects and the recovery of drugs and cash in Berea on Friday, 29 April. The team was following up on information regarding drugs that were kept in one of the houses on Currie Road in the Berea policing area. “Upon searching the premises, police found 110 pieces of rock cocaine and 11 loose packets of cocaine. The recovered drugs are valued at R25 300. Cash of R3 130, suspected to be the proceeds of drug sales, was also seized by police. The suspects appeared in the Durban Magistrate’s Court,” said police spokesperson, Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo.